---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="AI Setup Tutorial - Ollama + Claude Code">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero-badge">ü§ñ AI Setup Guide</span>
      <h1>Set Up Your <span class="gradient">AI Tools</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">Use Ollama + Claude Code to build your portfolio faster and smarter. Free, private, and powerful!</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;margin-top:28px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/templates" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Templates ‚Üí</a>
        <a href="/kids" class="btn btn-secondary">Kids Track</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- What you'll learn -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üìã What You'll Learn</h2>
        <div class="checklist">
          <div class="check-item"><span class="check">‚úÖ</span><p>Install and use Ollama (free local AI)</p></div>
          <div class="check-item"><span class="check">‚úÖ</span><p>Use Claude Code to customize your portfolio</p></div>
          <div class="check-item"><span class="check">‚úÖ</span><p>Connect the AI chat widget to real Ollama</p></div>
          <div class="check-item"><span class="check">‚úÖ</span><p>Generate content with AI prompts</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="prereqs">
          <span class="prereq-label">Prerequisites</span>
          <span class="prereq-item">üíª Any computer (Windows / Mac / Linux)</span>
          <span class="prereq-item">‚è±Ô∏è 30‚Äì45 minutes</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Part 1 -->
      <div class="part-header">
        <span class="part-num">Part 1</span>
        <h2>Install Ollama</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>ü¶ô What is Ollama?</h2>
        <p>Ollama is a free tool that runs AI locally on your computer ‚Äî no internet needed after installation, no subscriptions, completely private.</p>
        <div class="info-grid">
          <div class="info-item"><span class="info-icon">üí∞</span><h4>Free Forever</h4><p>No payments, no subscriptions</p></div>
          <div class="info-item"><span class="info-icon">üîí</span><h4>Private</h4><p>Your conversations stay on your computer</p></div>
          <div class="info-item"><span class="info-icon">‚ö°</span><h4>Works Offline</h4><p>No internet needed after install</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üì• Step 1.1 ‚Äî Download & Install</h2>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">1</span>
            <div><h4>Download Ollama</h4><p>Go to <a href="https://ollama.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ollama.com</a> and click <strong>Download</strong> for your OS</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">2</span>
            <div><h4>Run the installer</h4><p>Open the downloaded file and follow the steps ‚Äî it's like any other app</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">3</span>
            <div><h4>Open your terminal</h4><p>Windows: search "Command Prompt" ¬∑ Mac: search "Terminal"</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>ü§ñ Step 1.2 ‚Äî Download an AI Model</h2>
        <p>AI models are the "brains" that Ollama uses. This downloads about 2‚Äì4 GB ‚Äî grab a snack while you wait!</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code>ollama pull llama3.2</code></div>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üß™ Step 1.3 ‚Äî Test Ollama</h2>
        <div class="code-block"><code>ollama --version</code></div>
        <p style="margin-top:12px;">Then start the server:</p>
        <div class="code-block"><code>ollama serve</code></div>
        <div class="tip">üí° Keep Ollama running in the background while you work!</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Part 2 -->
      <div class="part-header">
        <span class="part-num">Part 2</span>
        <h2>Install Claude Code <span class="optional">(Optional)</span></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üß† What is Claude Code?</h2>
        <p>Claude Code is an AI coding assistant that lives in your terminal. You talk to it in plain English and it edits your code for you!</p>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">1</span>
            <div><h4>Install</h4><p>Run in your terminal:</p>
              <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:8px;"><code>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">2</span>
            <div><h4>Sign in</h4><p>Run <code>claude</code> and follow the sign-in link</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">3</span>
            <div><h4>Try it!</h4><p>Navigate to your project folder and ask Claude to help</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Part 3 -->
      <div class="part-header">
        <span class="part-num">Part 3</span>
        <h2>Customize with AI</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üí¨ Method A ‚Äî Claude Code</h2>
        <p>Open terminal in your portfolio folder and describe what you want:</p>
        <div class="code-block">
          <code>{`Update my portfolio with:
- Name: "Alex Chen"
- Location: "Tokyo, Japan"
- Skills: Python, JavaScript, Unity, Blender
- Projects:
  1. "TaskMaster" - React todo app
  2. "GameAI" - Python game
  3. "Portfolio" - Personal site
- Colors: Purple theme (#a855f7, #8b5cf6)`}</code>
        </div>
        <p>Claude edits your HTML file automatically!</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>ü¶ô Method B ‚Äî Ollama in Terminal</h2>
        <div class="code-block"><code>ollama run llama3.2</code></div>
        <p style="margin-top:12px;">Then ask it anything, like:</p>
        <div class="code-block">
          <code>{`Generate HTML for a skill card with icon üéÆ,
title 'Game Dev', description 'Creating games with Unity'`}</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üìã Method C ‚Äî Copy-Paste AI Prompts</h2>
        <p>Use these ready-made prompts with any AI:</p>

        <h3 style="margin:20px 0 8px;font-size:15px;color:var(--accent-secondary);">Change colors:</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <code>{`Replace the :root CSS variables in portfolio-basic/index.html with:
- --accent: #a855f7 (purple)
- --accent-secondary: #8b5cf6 (light purple)
- --bg-primary: #0f0f1a (dark purple bg)
- --bg-card: #1a1a2e (card bg)`}</code>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin:20px 0 8px;font-size:15px;color:var(--accent-secondary);">Add projects:</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <code>{`Generate HTML for 3 project cards:
1. "Weather App" - React weather app - tags: React, API
2. "Chat Bot" - Python Discord bot - tags: Python, AI
3. "Portfolio" - This portfolio - tags: HTML, CSS`}</code>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin:20px 0 8px;font-size:15px;color:var(--accent-secondary);">Generate a bio:</h3>
        <div class="code-block">
          <code>{`Write a 2-paragraph developer bio for someone who:
- Is named [YOUR NAME] from [YOUR CITY]
- Knows [YOUR SKILLS]
- Loves [YOUR INTERESTS]`}</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Part 4 -->
      <div class="part-header">
        <span class="part-num">Part 4</span>
        <h2>Connect AI Chat Widget</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üîå Link Ollama to Your Portfolio Chat</h2>
        <p>The AI portfolio template has a built-in chat widget. Here's how to connect it to your local Ollama!</p>

        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">1</span>
            <div><h4>Open portfolio-ai/index.html</h4><p>Use VS Code or any text editor</p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">2</span>
            <div><h4>Find the sendMessage function</h4><p>Search for <code>async function sendMessage</code></p></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <span class="step-num">3</span>
            <div><h4>Replace the fetch call</h4><p>Use the code below to connect to Ollama:</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <code>{`const response = await fetch('http://localhost:11434/api/generate', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    model: 'llama3.2',
    prompt: \`You are a portfolio AI for \${portfolioData.name}.
             Skills: \${portfolioData.skills.join(', ')}.
             User asked: \${text}
             Give a friendly, helpful answer:\`,
    stream: false
  })
});
const data = await response.json();
addMessage(data.response);`}</code>
        </div>
        <div class="tip">üí° Make sure <code>ollama serve</code> is running before testing the chat!</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Troubleshooting -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>üîß Troubleshooting</h2>
        <div class="trouble-grid">
          <div class="trouble-item">
            <h4>Ollama not starting?</h4>
            <div class="code-block"><code>tasklist | findstr ollama</code></div>
            <p>Check if it's already running in the background</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trouble-item">
            <h4>Chat not connecting?</h4>
            <p>1. Make sure <code>ollama serve</code> is running<br>2. Check URL is <code>http://localhost:11434</code><br>3. Try: <code>curl http://localhost:11434</code></p>
          </div>
          <div class="trouble-item">
            <h4>Claude Code not working?</h4>
            <p>Make sure you're in the project folder:<br><code>cd path/to/your/portfolio</code><br>Then try: <code>claude "help me"</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Done! -->
      <div class="done-card">
        <h2>üéâ You're All Set!</h2>
        <p>Now you can use AI to build and customize anything. Next step ‚Äî pick a template and make it yours!</p>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;margin-top:24px;">
          <a href="/templates" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Templates ‚Üí</a>
          <a href="/kids" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to Kids Track</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="navigation">
        <a href="/kids" class="btn btn-secondary">‚Üê Kids Track</a>
        <a href="/templates" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Templates ‚Üí</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero { padding: 100px 0 60px; text-align: center; }
  .lead { font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .content { padding: 40px 0 80px; }

  .part-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; margin: 48px 0 16px; }
  .part-num { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), var(--violet)); color: #fff; font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 100px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .part-header h2 { font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif; font-size: 22px; margin: 0; }
  .optional { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  .checklist { display: grid; gap: 12px; margin-top: 16px; }
  .check-item { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: center; }
  .check { font-size: 18px; }
  .check-item p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin: 0; }

  .prereqs { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin-top: 24px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); align-items: center; }
  .prereq-label { font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-secondary); }
  .prereq-item { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 100px; padding: 4px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  .info-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .info-item { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border-radius: 12px; padding: 16px; text-align: center; }
  .info-icon { font-size: 28px; display: block; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .info-item h4 { font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .info-item p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  .tip { margin-top: 16px; padding: 12px 16px; background: rgba(74,240,232,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(74,240,232,0.2); border-radius: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--accent-secondary); }

  .trouble-grid { display: grid; gap: 20px; margin-top: 16px; }
  .trouble-item h4 { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--accent); }
  .trouble-item p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 8px; line-height: 1.7; }
  .trouble-item code { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; }

  .done-card { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255,107,157,0.1), rgba(168,85,247,0.1)); border: 1px solid rgba(255,107,157,0.2); border-radius: 24px; padding: 48px 32px; text-align: center; margin: 32px 0; }
  .done-card h2 { font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .done-card p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 16px; }

  code { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace; font-size: 13px; color: var(--accent-secondary); }
  .lesson-card a { color: var(--accent-secondary); }
  .lesson-card h3 { font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif; }
</style>
